{"title_page": "Blacklorg Hill", "text_new": "{{Infobox mountain\n| name = Blacklorg Hill\n| photo = Blacklorg.jpg\n| photo_caption =\n| elevation_m = 681\n| elevation_ref = <ref name=\"hill-bagging1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hill-bagging.co.uk/mountaindetails.php?rf=1749 |title=Blacklorg Hill |publisher=Hill-bagging.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n| title=\n| prominence_m = 148\n| prominence_ref = <ref name=\"hill-bagging1\"/>\n| listing = Hu,Tu,Sim,[[Donald (hill)|D]],sMa,GT,DN,Y <ref name=\"hills-database1\">{{cite web|author=Chris Crocker |url=http://www.hills-database.co.uk/database_notes.html#classification |title=Database of British and Irish Hills: user guide |publisher=Hills-database.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n| translation =\n| language =\n| pronunciation =\n| location = [[East Ayrshire]], [[Dumfries and Galloway]], [[Scotland]]\n| range = [[Carsphairn and Scaur Hills]], [[Southern Uplands]]\n| coordinates =\n| grid_ref_UK = NS 65392 04237\n| topo = [[Ordnance Survey|OS]] ''Landranger'' 77\n| easiest_route =\n}}\n\n'''Blacklorg Hill''' is a hill in the [[Carsphairn and Scaur Hills]], part of the [[Southern Uplands]] of [[Scotland]]. It lies southeast of the town of [[New Cumnock]] in [[Ayrshire]], directly east of the Afton Reservoir. It is most frequently climbed along with the neighbouring hills, starting from the Glen Afton road.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hill-bagging.co.uk/mountaindetails.php?qu=DN&rf=1749 |title=Blacklorg Hill |publisher=Hill-bagging.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\n==Subsidiary [[Scottish Mountaineering Club|SMC]] Summits==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Summit !! Height (m) !! Listing <ref name=\"hills-database1\"/>\n|-\n| Meikledodd Hill || 643 || Tu,Sim,DT,GT,DN<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hill-bagging.co.uk/mountaindetails.php?qu=S&rf=1758 |title=Meikledodd Hill |publisher=Hill-bagging.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\